# data-models

## Core Data Models

### 1. Meeting Model
Importance Score: 90/100

Primary attributes:
- Thread ID for LangSmith tracing/analytics
- Signal mappings for extracted insights
- Knowledge relationships to DIKW items 
- Parent/child meeting relationships
- Meeting bundle associations

Business Rules:
- 24-hour conversation retention policy
- Command frequency-based suggestion prioritization
- Context preservation through thread IDs
- Structured feedback collection

### 2. Document Model  
Importance Score: 85/100

Primary attributes:
- Document type classification
- Semantic embeddings for search
- Knowledge graph relationships
- Version history tracking
- Synthesis status flags

Business Rules:
- Automatic DIKW level assignment
- Bidirectional meeting linkages
- Template-based signal extraction
- Knowledge synthesis triggers

## Relationship Structure

